# Database Migrations

This directory contains Alembic database migrations for the Classroom Token Hub application.

## Overview

Single-database configuration for Flask using Alembic for database schema version control.

## Quick Commands

```bash
# Create a new migration after model changes
flask db migrate -m "Description of changes"

# Apply migrations to database
flask db upgrade

# Revert last migration
flask db downgrade

# View migration history
flask db history
```

## Documentation

For detailed information about managing migrations, including:
- Resolving migration conflicts
- Consolidating migration history
- Troubleshooting migration issues

See: [docs/development/MIGRATION_GUIDE.md](../docs/development/MIGRATION_GUIDE.md)

## Migration Best Practices

- Always review auto-generated migrations before applying
- Test migrations on a backup database first
- Never edit migrations that have been committed to main
- Use descriptive migration messages
- Check for data loss before applying destructive changes
